The Data Analyst will work with FIND’s implementation team and identified partners in the 10 identified states to support the implementation of diagnostics network optimization projects aimed at increasing access to diagnostic services in these states and to inform new diagnostics development and roll-out strategies.

The Data Analyst will be expected to use analytical and quantitative methods to understand, predict and enhance processes to optimize access to health diagnostic services and communicate their outputs using data visualization and detailed reports.

